text: Jean-Marie Zoellé (16 November 1944 - 6 April 2020) was a French politician. He was Mayor of Saint-Louis, Haut-Rhin from 2011 until his death. He was Deputy Mayor from 1989 until 2011. Zoellé died on 6 April 2020 at a hospital in Bonn, Germany from COVID-19, aged 75.Haut-Rhin : le maire de Saint-Louis, Jean-Marie Zoellé, est mort du coronavirus ==References== Category:1944 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Germany Category:French mayors
